<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837E7E01A7E4FED2B37A6C1A" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1888" box="[1203,1351,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837E7E01A7E4FED2B37A6C1A" box="[1203,1351,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">M. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837E7E01A629FED2B6CB6CF7" authorityName="G. Q. Liu &amp; Q. Liu" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutulus">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837E7E01A629FED2B6CB6CF7" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">M. acutulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are nearly sympatric. The host plant of 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837E7E01A1E2FEF6B5756CF6" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1888" box="[693,840,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837E7E01A1E2FEF6B5756CF6" box="[693,840,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">M. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unknown so far.
</paragraph>
